data.title: @drawinggoose on Tumblr
data.meta_description: Lots of multi-fandom content, some personal artwork, plenty of art/history/literature ogling and the eternity of honking. Gothic horror is my muse.
data.text: Okay yes Stoker’s Dracula and the Bela Lugosi movie are phenomenal, but I’m tired of them dominating the canon. Give me vampires à la Carmilla. Give me creatures lusting after life and forming passionate relationships with their victims out of a desperate desire to feel alive again, to love and be loved again, to feel the warmth of another’s arms and the touch of their velvet lips and the heated flush of their cheeks. Give me passion that could be genuine love or just the desperation of one starved of humanity, where I’ll never know which is real and I won’t care because it’s a thick, dark wine I can’t stop drinking deeply of. Give me a passion that terrifies and intoxicates in equal measure. Give me a creature whose only crime is clutching at the humanity they will never regain, desperately pulling at the nearest sources of life in search of a companion who will breathe life into their lungs and set their heart racing again, a creature I cannot view as a villain but do not know whether or how to mourn, a creature whose coffin is filled not with earth but with blood: that they might be nearer that which they desire, that they might absorb the humanity they have lost in the act of drinking and bathing in the life of those they have desired, those they have perhaps truly loved. Give me mad passion, irreparably twisted morals, not lust nor malice but the core desire of every human heart: the simple desire to live.
